{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place sugar in mixing bowl and grind to icing sugar <nobr>15 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a plate and set aside.","Place biscuits in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>6 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place hazelnuts and pistachios in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>6 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to bowl with biscuits.","Place dark chocolate, milk chocolate and coconut oil in mixing bowl then melt <nobr>3 min\/50°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl and melt again <nobr>2 min\/50°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add reserved chopped nuts and biscuits then mix <nobr>20 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer to a shallow bowl and chill in fridge for 45 minutes until mixture is firmer.","Halve the chilled mixture and roll each piece on cling film into a sausage shape (25 cm long, Ø 4 cm). Wrap logs in cling film, sealing the ends. Chill in fridge for at least 3 hours until set.","Carefully remove cling film then roll logs in icing sugar until each log looks like a salami. Wrap in cling film or pack as a present, then store in fridge. Remove from fridge 1 hour before serving in slices (1-2 cm)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g caster sugar","150 g rich tea biscuits, halved","100 g hazelnuts","50 g pistachio nuts, unsalted, shelled","200 g dark chocolate, pieces or callets","100 g milk chocolate, pieces or callets","150 g coconut oil","icing sugar, for rolling"]}],"id":"r84811","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-oq2aYaAIYa4\/XZanH-chCLI\/AAAAAAAAg6c\/37IBjwLGUD0pNdNYSMnBysL0eRKbbPv7ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2quv0xeBakZ7lYoR.png","title":"Chocolate Salami","publishedAt":"2015-05-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"56.6 g","fat":"383 g","uom":"per 0 total recipe","carbohydrates":"381.6 g","calories":"21765 kJ \/ 5202 kcal"},"usefulItems":"shallow bowl or dish, cling film, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["An Italian and Portuguese dessert, which resembles a meat salami once finished, is made from dark chocolate, broken biscuits, butter and eggs. We think this recipe provides a fantastic treat to finish off any meal.","Try varying the nuts or adding raisins or dried cherries to the mixture.","For a boozy version, add 2 Tbsp rum, brandy or amaretto in Step 5."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","4h 5m","1 total recipe"]}